    <briefdescription>
<para>Client-side handle for a server-hosted Tryll agent. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>An <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_agent_proxy" kindref="compound">Tryll::Client::AgentProxy</ref> is returned by <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_tryll_client_1a8f84f0c4a65157becd4c332ea5acbd60" kindref="member">Tryll::Client::TryllClient::CreateAgent</ref> (or its async twin) and represents one agent running a workflow graph on the server. All turn-driving APIs live on the proxy; the owning <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_tryll_client" kindref="compound">Tryll::Client::TryllClient</ref> handles the underlying session.</para>
<sect1 id="_agent_proxy_8h_1autotoc_md0_1s1"><sect2 id="_agent_proxy_8h_1autotoc_md0">
<title>Callback-first model</title><para>All streaming output and turn lifecycle events are delivered through three persistent per-agent callbacks:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>SetOnAnswerText — streaming text chunks as they arrive.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SetOnTurnComplete — turn outcome (status, diagnostics, token count).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SetOnError — server-reported or disconnect errors.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SetOnToolCall — tool-call notifications from the graph (typed wrapper over <computeroutput>NodeEvent</computeroutput> <computeroutput>event_type=&quot;tool_call&quot;</computeroutput>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SetOnIntentClassified — intent-classification notifications (typed wrapper over <computeroutput>NodeEvent</computeroutput> <computeroutput>event_type=&quot;intent_classified&quot;</computeroutput>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SetOnNodeEvent — fallback for any other <computeroutput>NodeEvent</computeroutput> <computeroutput>event_type</computeroutput> or for events whose typed callback is not set.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>SendText is fire-and-forget; it enqueues the message and returns immediately. Register the callbacks before the first SendText call.</para>
<para>This model also covers server-initiated turns (e.g. voice autosend after VoiceInput::EndUtterance): those turns carry <computeroutput>agent_id</computeroutput> but no client-side <computeroutput>request_id</computeroutput>, and are delivered through the same persistent callbacks. </para>
</sect2></sect1>
